# .trivyignore — hermes-agent / hermes-agent-dev (context: apps/hermes-agent)
# Added 2026-07-18 after the first hermes-agent scan (run 29650965148)
# gated red. Trivy false positives — investigated, not silenced blindly.
#
# CVE-2022-25235 / CVE-2022-25236 (expat, bundled in the "firefox"
# package): the exact false positive already documented in
# apps/firefox/.trivyignore — this image installs Firefox for the
# dashboard kiosk via the same packages.mozilla.org repo + apt-pin
# pattern. Trivy's Ubuntu OS-package DB tracks vulnerabilities for the
# distro's own "firefox" package, which since Ubuntu 22.04+ is a
# transitional stub that just installs the snap, versioned
# "1:1snap1-0ubuntu1" — the epoch (1:) makes it dpkg-compare as newer
# than ANY real Mozilla .deb build (ours has version scheme
# "<version>~buildN", no epoch), so Trivy always reports our real,
# up-to-date Firefox as vulnerable to these two 2022 CVEs.
# Documented, reproduced elsewhere: aquasecurity/trivy discussion #6792
# (https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy/discussions/6792).
#
# Re-evaluate if Trivy changes how it resolves third-party .deb Firefox
# builds, or if these CVE IDs start showing up with a different
# (non-snap) fixed version. Keep in sync with apps/firefox/.trivyignore
# and apps/devtools/.trivyignore — all three carry this same pair.
CVE-2022-25235
CVE-2022-25236
